{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850135242,"sessionID":"ses_287157b99ffeVt3FR2F2b5mIJR","part":{"id":"prt_d78ea9b03001YeyGS6Cq4Efaw2","messageID":"msg_d78ea9248001putzOhUMan3XOV","sessionID":"ses_287157b99ffeVt3FR2F2b5mIJR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b2a7f74ef2d04cf9b4e8674fa6e9f5a3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: **Feature:** AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n4: **Goal:** Implement Kubernetes-native reconciler controllers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs using controller-runtime to provide automated lifecycle management for sandbox resources with proper event handling and status reporting.\n5: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n6: - AgentRuntimeReconciler successfully creates and manages sandbox resources\n7: - CodeInterpreterReconciler successfully creates and manages sandbox resources\n8: - Status conditions are accurately updated during reconciliation (Ready, Error, Progressing, etc.)\n9: - Finalizers are properly handled for resource deletion\n10: - Events are recorded for all significant operations\n11: - Metrics are exposed and can be scraped by Prometheus\n12: - Unit tests cover all major code paths\n13: - Integration tests validate end-to-end reconciliation\n14: - Error handling is robust and provides clear feedback\n15: - Reconciler can handle spec changes gracefully\n16: - Leader election works correctly in HA deployments\n17: **Architecture:** Controller-runtime based reconciler pattern with separate reconcilers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs, coexisting with existing HTTP-based controller, using agent-sandbox API for sandbox lifecycle management.\n18: **Tech Stack:** Go, controller-runtime, client-go, agent-sandbox API, Prometheus metrics, Ginkgo/Gomega testing\n19: **前端验证:** No\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ### Task 1: Create reconciler package directory structure\n24: \n25: **Files:**\n26: - Create: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/`\n27: \n28: **Step 1: Create reconciler directory**\n29: \n30: ```bash\n31: mkdir -p pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler\n32: ```\n33: \n34: **Step 2: Verify directory created**\n35: \n36: Run: `ls -la pkg/workloadmanager/controller/`\n37: Expected: Output shows reconciler/ directory\n38: \n39: **Step 3: Create package documentation file**\n40: \n41: ```go\n42: // Package reconciler implements Kubernetes reconciler controllers for\n43: // AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs using controller-runtime.\n44: //\n45: // The reconcilers watch for changes to CRDs and automatically manage\n46: // the lifecycle of associated sandbox resources.\n47: package reconciler\n48: ```\n49: \n50: **Step 4: Commit**\n51: \n52: ```bash\n53: git add pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/doc.go\n54: git commit -m \"feat(ar-007): create reconciler package structure\"\n55: ```\n56: \n57: ### Task 2: Define reconciler types and interfaces\n58: \n59: **Files:**\n60: - Create: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/types.go`\n61: \n62: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n63: \n64: ```go\n65: // pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/types_test.go\n66: package reconciler\n67: \n68: import (\n69: \t\"testing\"\n70: \n71: \t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n72: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n73: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/types\"\n74: \tctrl \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n75: )\n76: \n77: func TestReconcilerInterface(t *testing.T) {\n78: \tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n79: \n80: \tvar _ Reconciler = (*AgentRuntimeReconciler)(nil)\n81: \tvar _ Reconciler = (*CodeInterpreterReconciler)(nil)\n82: \tg.Expect(true).To(BeTrue())\n83: }\n84: \n85: func TestControllerConfig(t *testing.T) {\n86: \tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n87: \n88: \tcfg := &ControllerConfig{\n89: \t\tRequeueAfter:          10 * time.Second,\n90: \t\tMaxConcurrentReconciles: 2,\n91: \t}\n92: \n93: \tg.Expect(cfg.RequeueAfter).To(Equal(10 * time.Second))\n94: \tg.Expect(cfg.MaxConcurrentReconciles).To(Equal(2))\n95: }\n96: ```\n97: \n98: **Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n99: \n100: Run: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestReconcilerInterface -v`\n101: Expected: FAIL with \"undefined: Reconciler\" and \"undefined: AgentRuntimeReconciler\"\n102: \n103: **Step 3: Write minimal implementation**\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: package reconciler\n107: \n108: import (\n109: \t\"time\"\n110: \n111: \t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n112: )\n113: \n114: // Reconciler defines the interface for all reconcilers\n115: type Reconciler interface {\n116: \tReconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n117: \tSetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error\n118: }\n119: \n120: // ControllerConfig provides configuration for reconcilers\n121: type ControllerConfig struct {\n122: \t// RequeueAfter is the default requeue interval\n123: \tRequeueAfter time.Duration\n124: \n125: \t// MaxConcurrentReconciles is the maximum number of concurrent reconciles\n126: \tMaxConcurrentReconciles int\n127: \n128: \t// SyncPeriod is the full resync period\n129: \tSyncPeriod *time.Duration\n130: \n131: \t// EnableLeaderElection enables leader election\n132: \tEnableLeaderElection bool\n133: \n134: \t// LeaderElectionID is the leader election ID\n135: \tLeaderElectionID string\n136: \n137: \t// LeaderElectionNamespace is the namespace for leader election\n138: \tLeaderElectionNamespace string\n139: \n140: \t// MetricsAddr is the metrics server address\n141: \tMetricsAddr string\n142: \n143: \t// EnableProfiling enables profiling endpoints\n144: \tEnableProfiling bool\n145: \n146: \t// ProbeAddr is the health probe address\n147: \tProbeAddr string\n148: }\n149: \n150: // AgentRuntimeReconciler reconciles AgentRuntime resources\n151: type AgentRuntimeReconciler struct {\n152: \t// Implementation to be added in subsequent tasks\n153: }\n154: \n155: // CodeInterpreterReconciler reconciles CodeInterpreter resources\n156: type CodeInterpreterReconciler struct {\n157: \t// Implementation to be added in subsequent tasks\n158: }\n159: ```\n160: \n161: **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n162: \n163: Run: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestReconcilerInterface -v`\n164: Expected: PASS\n165: \n166: **Step 5: Commit**\n167: \n168: ```bash\n169: git add pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/types.go pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/types_test.go\n170: git commit -m \"feat(ar-007): define reconciler types and interfaces\"\n171: ```\n172: \n173: ### Task 3: Define status condition types and constants\n174: \n175: **Files:**\n176: - Create: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status.go`\n177: \n178: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n179: \n180: ```go\n181: // pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status_test.go\n182: package reconciler\n183: \n184: import (\n185: \t\"testing\"\n186: \n187: \t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n188: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n189: )\n190: \n191: func TestConditionTypes(t *testing.T) {\n192: \tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n193: \n194: \tg.Expect(ConditionTypeReady).To(Equal(\"Ready\"))\n195: \tg.Expect(ConditionTypeAvailable).To(Equal(\"Available\"))\n196: \tg.Expect(ConditionTypeProgressing).To(Equal(\"Progressing\"))\n197: \tg.Expect(ConditionTypeError).To(Equal(\"Error\"))\n198: \tg.Expect(ConditionTypeSandboxCreated).To(Equal(\"SandboxCreated\"))\n199: }\n200: \n201: func TestReasonConstants(t *testing.T) {\n202: \tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n203: \n204: \tg.Expect(ReasonReconciliationStarted).To(Equal(\"ReconciliationStarted\"))\n205: \tg.Expect(ReasonSandboxCreated).To(Equal(\"SandboxCreated\"))\n206: \tg.Expect(ReasonValidationFailed).To(Equal(\"ValidationFailed\"))\n207: }\n208: ```\n209: \n210: **Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n211: \n212: Run: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestConditionTypes -v`\n213: Expected: FAIL with \"undefined: ConditionTypeReady\"\n214: \n215: **Step 3: Write minimal implementation**\n216: \n217: ```go\n218: package reconciler\n219: \n220: import (\n221: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n222: )\n223: \n224: // Condition types for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n225: const (\n226: \t// ConditionTypeReady indicates the resource is ready to serve requests\n227: \tConditionTypeReady = \"Ready\"\n228: \n229: \t// ConditionTypeAvailable indicates the runtime is available\n230: \tConditionTypeAvailable = \"Available\"\n231: \n232: \t// ConditionTypeProgressing indicates the resource is being reconciled\n233: \tConditionTypeProgressing = \"Progressing\"\n234: \n235: \t// ConditionTypeError indicates an error occurred during reconciliation\n236: \tConditionTypeError = \"Error\"\n237: \n238: \t// ConditionTypeSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox resource was created\n239: \tConditionTypeSandboxCreated = \"SandboxCreated\"\n240: )\n241: \n242: // Reason constants\n243: const (\n244: \t// Reconciliation reasons\n245: \tReasonReconciliationStarted = \"ReconciliationStarted\"\n246: \tReasonReconciliationComplete = \"ReconciliationComplete\"\n247: \tReasonReconciliationFailed = \"ReconciliationFailed\"\n248: \n249: \t// Sandbox creation reasons\n250: \tReasonSandboxCreating = \"SandboxCreating\"\n251: \tReasonSandboxCreated = \"SandboxCreated\"\n252: \tReasonSandboxCreateFailed = \"SandboxCreateFailed\"\n253: \tReasonSandboxUpdating = \"SandboxUpdating\"\n254: \tReasonSandboxUpdated = \"SandboxUpdated\"\n255: \tReasonSandboxUpdateFailed = \"SandboxUpdateFailed\"\n256: \tReasonSandboxDeleting = \"SandboxDeleting\"\n257: \tReasonSandboxDeleted = \"SandboxDeleted\"\n258: \tReasonSandboxDeleteFailed = \"SandboxDeleteFailed\"\n259: \n260: \t// Validation reasons\n261: \tReasonValidationFailed = \"ValidationFailed\"\n262: \tReasonSpecInvalid = \"SpecInvalid\"\n263: \n264: \t// Cleanup reasons\n265: \tReasonCleanupFailed = \"CleanupFailed\"\n266: )\n267: \n268: // SetCondition sets a condition on the resource status\n269: func SetCondition(conditions *[]metav1.Condition, conditionType, reason, message string, status metav1.ConditionStatus, timestamp metav1.Time) {\n270: \t// Implementation in subsequent tasks\n271: }\n272: \n273: // GetCondition gets a condition of the specified type\n274: func GetCondition(conditions []metav1.Condition, conditionType string) *metav1.Condition {\n275: \t// Implementation in subsequent tasks\n276: \treturn nil\n277: }\n278: \n279: // IsReady returns true if the resource is ready\n280: func IsReady(conditions []metav1.Condition) bool {\n281: \t// Implementation in subsequent tasks\n282: \treturn false\n283: }\n284: ```\n285: \n286: **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n287: \n288: Run: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestConditionTypes -v`\n289: Expected: PASS\n290: \n291: **Step 5: Commit**\n292: \n293: ```bash\n294: git add pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status.go pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status_test.go\n295: git commit -m \"feat(ar-007): define status condition types and constants\"\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ### Task 4: Implement status condition management functions\n299: \n300: **Files:**\n301: - Modify: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status.go`\n302: \n303: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n304: \n305: ```go\n306: // pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status_test.go\n307: func TestSetCondition(t *testing.T) {\n308: \tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n309: \n310: \tvar conditions []metav1.Condition\n311: \tnow := metav1.Now()\n312: \n313: \tSetCondition(&conditions, ConditionTypeReady, \"ReadyReason\", \"Ready message\", metav1.ConditionTrue, now)\n314: \n315: \tg.Expect(conditions).To(HaveLen(1))\n316: \tg.Expect(conditions[0].Type).To(Equal(ConditionTypeReady))\n317: \tg.Expect(conditions[0].Status).To(Equal(metav1.ConditionTrue))\n318: \tg.Expect(conditions[0].Reason).To(Equal(\"ReadyReason\"))\n319: \tg.Expect(conditions[0].Message).To(Equal(\"Ready message\"))\n320: }\n321: \n322: func TestGetCondition(t *testing.T) {\n323: \tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n324: \n325: \tconditions := []metav1.Condition{\n326: \t\t{\n327: \t\t\tType:   ConditionTypeReady,\n328: \t\t\tStatus: metav1.ConditionTrue,\n329: \t\t},\n330: \t}\n331: \n332: \tcondition := GetCondition(conditions, ConditionTypeReady)\n333: \tg.Expect(condition).NotTo(BeNil())\n334: \tg.Expect(condition.Type).To(Equal(ConditionTypeReady))\n335: \n336: \tcondition = GetCondition(conditions, ConditionTypeError)\n337: \tg.Expect(condition).To(BeNil())\n338: }\n339: \n340: func TestIsReady(t *testing.T) {\n341: \tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n342: \n343: \tconditions := []metav1.Condition{\n344: \t\t{\n345: \t\t\tType:   ConditionTypeReady,\n346: \t\t\tStatus: metav1.ConditionTrue,\n347: \t\t},\n348: \t}\n349: \n350: \tg.Expect(IsReady(conditions)).To(BeTrue())\n351: \n352: \tconditions[0].Status = metav1.ConditionFalse\n353: \tg.Expect(IsReady(conditions)).To(BeFalse())\n354: }\n355: ```\n356: \n357: **Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n358: \n359: Run: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestSetCondition -v`\n360: Expected: FAIL with SetCondition not setting conditions correctly\n361: \n362: **Step 3: Write minimal implementation**\n363: \n364: ```go\n365: // SetCondition sets a condition on the resource status\n366: func SetCondition(conditions *[]metav1.Condition, conditionType, reason, message string, status metav1.ConditionStatus, timestamp metav1.Time) {\n367: \t// Find existing condition\n368: \texistingIndex := -1\n369: \tfor i, c := range *conditions {\n370: \t\tif c.Type == conditionType {\n371: \t\t\texistingIndex = i\n372: \t\t\tbreak\n373: \t\t}\n374: \t}\n375: \n376: \t// Create new condition\n377: \tnewCondition := metav1.Condition{\n378: \t\tType:               conditionType,\n379: \t\tStatus:             status,\n380: \t\tReason:             reason,\n381: \t\tMessage:            message,\n382: \t\tLastTransitionTime: timestamp,\n383: \t}\n384: \n385: \t// Update or append\n386: \tif existingIndex >= 0 {\n387: \t\t// Only update transition time if status changed\n388: \t\tif (*conditions)[existingIndex].Status != status {\n389: \t\t\t(*conditions)[existingIndex].LastTransitionTime = timestamp\n390: \t\t}\n391: \t\t(*conditions)[existingIndex] = newCondition\n392: \t} else {\n393: \t\t*conditions = append(*conditions, newCondition)\n394: \t}\n395: }\n396: \n397: // GetCondition gets a condition of the specified type\n398: func GetCondition(conditions []metav1.Condition, conditionType string) *metav1.Condition {\n399: \tfor i := range conditions {\n400: \t\tif conditions[i].Type == conditionType {\n401: \t\t\treturn &conditions[i]\n402: \t\t}\n403: \t}\n404: \treturn nil\n405: }\n406: \n407: // IsReady returns true if the resource is ready\n408: func IsReady(conditions []metav1.Condition) bool {\n409: \tcondition := GetCondition(conditions, ConditionTypeReady)\n410: \treturn condition != nil && condition.Status == metav1.ConditionTrue\n411: }\n412: ```\n413: \n414: **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n415: \n416: Run: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestSetCondition -v`\n417: Expected: PASS\n418: \n419: **Step 5: Commit**\n420: \n421: ```bash\n422: git add pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status.go pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status_test.go\n423: git commit -m \"feat(ar-007): implement status condition management functions\"\n424: ```\n425: \n426: ### Task 5: Define finalizer constants and utilities\n427: \n428: **Files:**\n429: - Create: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/finalizers.go`\n430: \n431: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n432: \n433: ```go\n434: // pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/finalizers_test.go\n435: pac